In addition to the absolute percentage of haste, there is a minimum weapon speed cap, set at 14. <br>
<br>
In essence, haste is capped at 175% of normal attack speed, OR 14 effective delay, whichever comes first. <br>
<br>
A 21 delay weapon bangs into that 14 delay cap pretty fast, where a 50 delay weapon does not, and can take full advantage of the spell/item effects. <br>
<br>
Even though there are a few weapons in the game that have delay lower than 14, it's hardcoded to make them swing no faster than once every 1.4 seconds.<br>
<br>
This too was intentional, to both limit the absolute effectiveness of 1h weapons, and to add value to the 2h weapons, and giving you a greater range of tactical choices to make. <br>
<br>
Expansion will change this minimum delay as well, for some classes <br>
